{"art": [], "author": [{"email_address": "truthometer@politifact.com", "first_name": "Maryna", "id": 739, "last_name": "Dorosh", "name_slug": "maryna-dorosh", "on_staff_page": null, "phone": "", "photo": null, "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/739/", "title": "Visiting Fellow", "twitter": ""}], "canonical_url": "/facebook-fact-checks/statements/2018/sep/24/blog-posting/false-dian-feinstein-quote-about-gunman-comes-back/", "edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Facebook", "edition": "Facebook fact-checks", "edition_slug": "facebook-fact-checks", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 63, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "Facebook fact-checks Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/63/"}, "editor": [{"email_address": "asharockman@politifact.com", "first_name": "Aaron", "id": 114, "last_name": "Sharockman", "name_slug": "aaron-sharockman", "on_staff_page": 2, "phone": "727-553-4534", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/staffers/zwPolitifactHeadshots05.JPG", "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/114/", "title": "Executive Director", "twitter": "asharock"}], "facebook_headline": "False Dianne Feinstein quote about gunman comes back again", "id": 15908, "in_future": false, "is_pundit": false, "make_public": true, "preview": true, "researcher": [{"email_address": "truthometer@politifact.com", "first_name": "Maryna", "id": 739, "last_name": "Dorosh", "name_slug": "maryna-dorosh", "on_staff_page": null, "phone": "", "photo": null, "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/739/", "title": "Visiting Fellow", "twitter": ""}], "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statement/15908/", "ruling": {"adkey": "Truth-O-Meter", "advalue": "Pants on Fire", "id": 6, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementruling/6/", "ruling": "Pants on Fire!", "ruling_graphic": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/rulings/tom-pantsonfire.gif", "ruling_slug": "pants-fire"}, "ruling_comments": "<p>A quote allegedly from Sen. Dianne Feinstein, D-Calif., saying gunmen will lay down their weapons when they see their victims are unarmed is&nbsp;fabricated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The page Principle News shared the quote in a post on Sept. 17.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It quotes Feinstein as saying, &quot;When the gunman realizes that nobody else is armed, he will lay down his weapons and turn himself in. That&#39;s human nature.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/PLhBjL4fQfNf6TBPbSNuwKR1_dgryu00dZICgdC3GCuMZiEjGPYC3wVpgNK3A4YsJs6EW4cGG2xH-0FrB5Su00-YgOheYb8SmOjyKfESgOu8IoEQhYM26YC1-41Kk9DAOBDHsdoU\" style=\"border:none; height:331px; width:602px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This image was flagged as part of Facebook&rsquo;s efforts to combat false news and misinformation on its News Feed. (Read more about our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/help/1952307158131536?helpref=related\">partnership with Facebook</a>.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The statement&nbsp;on the meme about gunman is a&nbsp;fabricated quote that first appeared February 2013&nbsp;on the website Palookaville Post. The story appeared after Feinstein proposed a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.feinstein.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/assault-weapons-ban-summary\">bill</a> that would &quot;ban the sale, transfer, manufacturing or importation of 150 specific firearms.&quot;&nbsp;The material from the Palookaville Post article was quoted on <a href=\"https://theblacksphere.net/2013/02/feinstein-and-boxer-ask-californians-to-lay-down-their-weapons-during-statewide-manhunt/\">several</a> <a href=\"http://patriotoutdoornews.com/5405/feinstein-and-boxer-ask-californians-to-lay-down-their-weapons-during-statewide-manhunt\">websites.</a> &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The original website doesn&rsquo;t operate now, but the full article can be found in the archive of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20130210084023/http:/www.palookavillepost.com/2013/02/07/feinstein-and-boxer-ask-californians-to-lay-down-their-weapons-during-statewide-manhunt/\">WayBack Machine.</a> &nbsp;It is bylined by a fake author&nbsp;&quot;Jimmy Olsentwins.&quot; The website itself was satirical and&nbsp;mostly active in 2013.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the next five years the false post bounced around the internet (especially in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/GunControlKills/photos/a.199201850149448/461639823905648/?type=3&amp;__xts__%5B0%5D=68.ARB_S_pEif5r0dofRFnSdGLcsIp3Q1Dnc5hz-Vmb9biqv85gjKpahdtJ19osn0uxmd7iniq2JfBR3dyOQ6JXDmVStx2Z_2gpJ3vDXgwpunADhTyjV-0lt7eiGkvicRpSOXHJpgZdbv73E5qTmWcGL4fpck-i8J2drhPezGrPE14FI6eYVp5M&amp;__tn__=H-R\">memes</a>) to criticize Feinstein.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We rate this claim Pants on Fire.</p>\r\n", "ruling_comments_date": "2018-09-24T17:28:57.050653", "ruling_date": "2018-09-24T17:53:42", "ruling_headline": "False Dianne Feinstein quote about gunman comes back again", "ruling_headline_slug": "false-dian-feinstein-quote-about-gunman-comes-back", "ruling_link_text": "A made-up quote", "ruling_state": null, "source_documents": null, "sources": "<p>Snopes,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://\u00a0https://www.snopes.com/fact-check/gunman-gambit/\">Dianne Feinstein &lsquo;Gunman&rsquo; Quote</a>, accessed Sept. 21, 2018</p>\r\n", "speaker": {"adkey": null, "advalue": null, "barely_true_count": 26, "current_job": "", "false_count": 87, "first_name": "", "half_true_count": 15, "home_state": "", "id": 43, "last_name": "Bloggers", "mostly_true_count": 10, "name_slug": "blog-posting", "pants_count": 279, "party": {"id": 2, "party": "None", "party_slug": "none", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/party/2/"}, "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/mugs/mug-bloggers.jpg", "primary_edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Punditfact", "edition": "PunditFact", "edition_slug": "punditfact", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 48, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "The PunditFact Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/48/"}, "promise_meter_cutout": null, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/person/43/", "total_count": 425, "true_count": 5, "website": ""}, "statement": "<p>Says that&nbsp;Dianne Feinstein said, &quot;When the gunman realizes that nobody else is armed, he will lay down his weapons and turn himself in&hellip;. that&rsquo;s just human nature.&quot;</p>\r\n", "statement_context": "an image on Facebook", "statement_date": "2018-09-24", "statement_type": {"id": 2, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementtype/2/", "statement_type": "Claim", "type_description": "blog post "}, "subject": [{"description": "<p>There&rsquo;s an interesting discussion happening now about the spread of fake news on the Internet and what companies like Facebook, Google and Twitter, among others, should do to stop it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That&rsquo;s a healthy conversation to have, and one we hope continues in the weeks and months ahead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But that doesn&rsquo;t mean we can&rsquo;t do something now. Here at PolitiFact, we&rsquo;re beefing up our coverage of fake news to help our readers better sort out fact from fiction on their social media feeds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The claims can be about anything -- politics, entertainment, a fishy-sounding medical cure.</p>\r\n", "id": 323, "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/subjects/mugs/fake.png", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/subject/323/", "subject": "Fake news", "subject_slug": "fake-news", "used_in_edition": ["/api/v/2/edition/56/", "/api/v/2/edition/49/", "/api/v/2/edition/53/", "/api/v/2/edition/4/", "/api/v/2/edition/5/", "/api/v/2/edition/60/", "/api/v/2/edition/61/", "/api/v/2/edition/50/", "/api/v/2/edition/51/", "/api/v/2/edition/1/", "/api/v/2/edition/59/", "/api/v/2/edition/57/", "/api/v/2/edition/47/", "/api/v/2/edition/13/", "/api/v/2/edition/55/", "/api/v/2/edition/58/", "/api/v/2/edition/7/", "/api/v/2/edition/9/", "/api/v/2/edition/54/", "/api/v/2/edition/48/", "/api/v/2/edition/6/", "/api/v/2/edition/14/", "/api/v/2/edition/2/", "/api/v/2/edition/10/", "/api/v/2/edition/8/"]}], "target": [], "twitter_headline": "False Dianne Feinstein quote about gunman comes back again"}